* detached (WIP)
:PROPERTIES:
:ARCHIVE_TIME: 2026-06-01 Mon 19:32
:ARCHIVE_FILE: ~/src/doomconfig/config.org
:ARCHIVE_OLPATH: Org Mode/org-babel
:ARCHIVE_CATEGORY: config
:END:
detached allows running shell commands detached from Emacs using dtach.
Commands continue running even if Emacs crashes, with full output history.

Fix consult
#+begin_src elisp :tangle no
(package! detached :recipe (:host sourcehut :repo "avph/detached.el") :pin "e4237ea6920b642cd30a460d532cff9ff84cf3e0")
#+end_src

#+begin_src elisp :tangle no
(use-package! detached
  :init
  (detached-init)
  :bind (;; Replace `async-shell-command' with `detached-shell-command'
         ([remap async-shell-command] . detached-shell-command)
         ;; Replace `compile' with `detached-compile'
         ([remap compile] . detached-compile)
         ([remap recompile] . detached-compile-recompile)
         ;; Replace built in completion of sessions with `consult'
         ([remap detached-open-session] . detached-consult-session))
  :custom ((detached-show-output-on-attach t)
           (detached-terminal-data-command system-type)))
#+end_src

** Usage with org-babel
[[https://sr.ht/~niklaseklund/detached.el/#org-babel][org-babel docs]]
Add =:detached t= header argument to shell source blocks:

#+begin_example
,#+begin_src sh :detached t
  # Long running command
  sleep 60 && echo "Done!"
,#+end_src

,#+RESULTS:
: [detached]
#+end_example

